The paper deals with local triangle counting in graph streams, which is a fundamental task in graph mining. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. The paper also discusses applications such as anomaly detection and social network analysis, which are typically associated with the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Social and Economic Networks (cs.SOC) categories. The paper proposes a method for reducing variance and handling duplicate edges, which suggests that it may also belong to the Statistical Learning (cs.SD) category. Finally, the paper deals with graph streams, which suggests that it may also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) category.
